Colombia Stocks: Bolsa de Valores, Grupo Suramericana, ETB

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-05-31T21:00:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/colombia-stocks-bolsa-de-valores-grupo-suramericana-etb.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IGBC Index rose 1.1 percent to 14,550.52, while the
Colcap Index rose 1.3 percent to 1,760.4.  Colombia ’s credit
rating was raised to investment grade by Moody’s Investors
Service, matching a move by Standard & Poor’s two months
earlier, as economic growth accelerates and the threat posed by
guerrilla groups and organized crime recedes.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia (BVC)  SA, the operator of
the country’s main securities exchange, rose 2.1 percent to 43.9
pesos, a fourth-month high, after trading began yesterday across
Colombian, Peruvian and Chilean bourses in  Latin America ’s first
international exchange integration.  Empresa de Telecomunicaciones de Bogota (ETB)  SA, the
state-run phone company serving Colombia’s capital, rose 4.6
percent to 710 pesos, a six-month high. The city is expected to
present a proposal to the Bogota city council as soon as this
week to sell part of its majority stake in the company,
newspaper El Tiempo reported, citing people it didn’t identify.  “There’s a lot of speculation the city will sell its stake
soon,” said Mauricio Restrepo del Toro, the head of research at
brokerage Bolsa y Renta.  Grupo de Inversiones Suramericana SA (GRUPOSUR)  , the
parent company of Colombia’s biggest bank, rose 3 percent to
39,980 pesos, a six-month high, on the Moody’s upgrade, said
David Pelaez, an analyst at Bolsa y Renta.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
